    "superresolution.screen.config.options.tooltip.inject_postChain_black_list": "Some mods use Post-chain for UI effects. Injecting into Post-chain may render UI at the world resolution, causing issues (e.g., blurry interfaces like ModernUI)\nAdd Post-chain names to exclude here; the mod will skip them during injection\nChanges may require a game restart to take effect",
    "superresolution.screen.config.options.tooltip.internal_texture_format": "Internal texture format precision affects VRAM usage. Higher precision uses more VRAM; lower precision uses less.\nNote: Too low precision may cause visible color banding",
    "superresolution.screen.config.options.tooltip.interop_sync_mode": "The mod uses OpenGL-Vulkan interop for super resolution processing (only for some algorithms, like DLSS). The interop sync mode determines how the mod handles resource synchronization between OpenGL and Vulkan.\nLow latency mode directly processes the current frame's image, synchronizing OpenGL and Vulkan, with lower latency but may reduce FPS in low-end scenarios.\nHigh performance mode allows Vulkan super resolution and OpenGL game rendering to proceed simultaneously, improving performance but increasing input latency.",
    "superresolution.screen.config.options.tooltip.sharpness": "Lower values make object edges more distinct\nHigher values make distant objects blurrier\nRecommended value: around 0.55",
    "superresolution.screen.config.options.tooltip.skip_init_vulkan": "Skipping Vulkan initialization may affect certain algorithms",
